Patient Safety 02

FLKUO

Harm


Psychological or physical injury/damage

  • Inevitable Harm

  • Preventable Harm

Error


Error and harm: Not all errors cause harm. Not all harm is caused by errors.

Examples

Hazard

  • A source of potential harm

Risk

  • Likelihood or chance that harm will occur if exposed to a hazard

  • Acceptable vs. Unacceptable Risk

Tools

  • Root Cause Analysis (RCA)

  • Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (FMEA)

  • FMEA vs. RCA

The aspects of the physical environment

  • Factors include:

    • Space and physical constraints
    • Lighting
    • Noise
    • Climate
    • Vibration
    • Electromagnetic radiation (Parsons, 2000)
